text.tspan: Content is Key
Onboarding
Access to Artist
Create Account/Login
Per the feedback collected during my usability
testing, users prefer to have some type of
onboarding process.
“Onboarding screens give
me a preview of the application before I
actually create an account and it weighs
heavily on my decision to create an account
or not.”
Majority of the users agreed that they
liked onboarding, but they want the option to
skip through it.
All 6 participants that were tested stated they
want the option to create an account or login
with their social media credentials. It allows them
to gain access quickly, and many of the other
apps function as such. The social media
preferences varied from person to person, but
my take-way was that this is a feature that all of
the participants appreciate and expecte.
A major takeaway that I gathered from my
usability testing, was participants want to be
flooded with content. I observed users selecting
the pictures that resonated with them which
helped facilitate their navigational journey.
“I am
very visual, so I like that this application is
picture oriented!”
When accessing the Artist profile, every
participant stated they need to have the ability
to communicate with the artist. They would like
to access their social media accounts, have the
ability to preview their portfolio, schedule
consultations/appointments, and get an overall
feel for whom the artist is.
